attachments.text: WIRED asked Werner Herzog, whose new film ‘Lo and Behold’ examines the information age of the Internet, to weigh in on tech manners.

text: How many antidepressants do you think that guy is on?
that’s what makes him so awesome
That peppy music is hiding something
Werner Herzog stares into the void, and the void is like “fuck this. This is too dark for me"
He’s like the next Chuck Morris joke

Great article on the lack of diversity and the incestuous, closed-loop strain of design the tech industry and internet culture perpetuates. Important in the sense that viewing good design through too narrow a lens can have the unfortunate side effect of diluting true diversity in culture. Such a good piece, I highly recommend taking the time to read it.
